http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Innovate-researchers-told/article14024269.ece

Chief Minister N. Chandrababu Naidu has appealed to students and researchers to think out of the box and come up with innovative ideas. In the same vein, he urged universities and teaching fraternity to collaborate with institutes of national and international repute to pioneer in path-breaking research.Speaking after launching the Andhra Pradesh Science Congress on the theme ‘Science for smart technologies’ on SVU campus here on Wednesday, Mr. Naidu promised all support on behalf of the State government for those coming up with innovative ideas.He recalled how videoconferencing and e-governance technologies introduced by him two decades ago had become popular later.The Congress presented Lifetime Achievement awards to ISRO Chairman A.S. Kiran Kumar, Asian Institute of Gastroenterology Chairman D. Nageshwar Reddy, Andhra Pradesh State Skill Development Corporation (APSSDC) Director K. Lakshminarayana, Centre for Cellular and Molecular Biology (CCMB) Director C. Mohan Rao and DST former Secretary P. Rama Rao.Ministers Bojjala Gopalakrishna Reddy (Environment and Forest), P. Narayana (Municipal Administration) and Ghanta Srinivasa Rao (Higher Education), Vice-Chancellors A. Damodaram (SVU) and V. Durga Bhavani (SPMVV) took part.Chief Minister launched Andhra Pradesh Science Congress on SVU campus